main event: Multiple UFO sightings and photographs were reported at Chitose Air Base, Japan in September 1957. The sightings included circular objects with wing or tail structures and an unidentified object in the sky that appeared to be hovering or moving slowly.
interesting points: The sighting involved multiple unidentified flying objects and included six photographs as evidence.
The circular objects observed in the photographs had a central circular region and what appeared to be a wing or tail structure extending from them.
Personnel of the Base Weather Station observed three objects in the sky over Chitose Air Base, which appeared to be hovering or moving slowly through breaks in the cloud cover.
The objects were observed for approximately 10 minutes, indicating a sustained sighting.
The report included specific details such as the date, time, and location of the sightings, adding credibility to the incident.
sighted object: multiple circular objects with wing or tail structures, unidentified object in the sky
witnesses: personnel of the Base Weather Station
photographs: yes, the report includes six photographs
